rsAddressPoolMIB.name: rsAddressPoolMIB

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

rsAddressPoolMIB.contactinfo: Redstone Communications, Inc. 5 Carlisle Road Westford MA 01886 USA Tel: +1-978-692-1999 Email: mib@redstonecom.com
rsAddressPoolMIB.description: The Address Pool MIB for the Redstone Communications Inc. enterprise.

rsAddressPoolTable.name: rsAddressPoolTable
rsAddressPoolTable.description: A table of IP address pools. Each pool describes a range of IP addresses available for assignment for dynamic connections.

rsAddressPoolEntry.name: rsAddressPoolEntry
rsAddressPoolEntry.description: An entry describing an IP address pool.

rsAddressPoolIndex.name: rsAddressPoolIndex
rsAddressPoolIndex.description: An arbitrary integer index that distinguishes this address pool.

rsAddressPoolRowStatus.name: rsAddressPoolRowStatus
rsAddressPoolRowStatus.description: Controls creation/deletion of address pools. Only value 'active' will be observed with GET. Only values 'createAndGo' and 'destroy' are supported for SET. Once created, entry content cannot be modified except by deleting and recreating an entry with the same index.

rsAddressPoolName.name: rsAddressPoolName
rsAddressPoolName.description: The name of this address pool.

rsAddressPoolStart.name: rsAddressPoolStart
rsAddressPoolStart.description: The starting IP address for the range of addresses comprising this pool.

rsAddressPoolEnd.name: rsAddressPoolEnd
rsAddressPoolEnd.description: The ending IP address for the range of addresses comprising this pool.

rsAddressPoolSize.name: rsAddressPoolSize
rsAddressPoolSize.description: The number of addresses available in this pool.

rsAddressPoolInUse.name: rsAddressPoolInUse
rsAddressPoolInUse.description: The number of addresses currently allocated from this pool.

rsAddressPoolCompliance.name: rsAddressPoolCompliance
rsAddressPoolCompliance.description: The compliance statement for systems providing local address pools.

rsAddressPoolGroup.name: rsAddressPoolGroup
rsAddressPoolGroup.description: The basic collection of objects providing management of local address pools.
